				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: The city´s main relationship the public and private interactions. In old age already studied these relations taking into account aspects, historical, cultural and social and community space, unlike the private area that already refers to obtaining capital. From there we have the relations of government and the private domain power.					<B>Objectives</B>: In light of this situation, it was chosen as the object of study Rua XV de Novembro de Curitiba. It contains various relationships public and private, as well as of "place" and "non-place", thanks to its strong historical context and changes with the intention to raise capital.
From this and the field of study of the way, it is possible to systematize the relations, tensions and track fields. It can be seen from this how the private power can literally make the government lose space on the road, and the opposite, ie the private power can also help to compose a public space quite interesting for the public domain					<B>Methods</B>: To analyze the way demonstrating the Public and Private relationship they were divided into six compartments the space that corresponds to the promenade Rua XV de Novembro. This will enable a better detailing of its characteristics, definition of place, identity, power relations and political domination domination of capital. Thus resulting in public relations and private street.					<B>Results</B>: In addition, there is clearly that there are public spaces in the public domain or
private domain, and private spaces of the private or public domain. In this way, the
relationships become very complex as can be seen in one of the compartments of the road
that the length of the queue more than one establishment dominates the public space
(public space with domain of private power) and affect the same. However, in another
block, the permanence of private power, alternative trades as frames, generates interest of
the people and their type of trade makes the public space much more interesting and
contributes to cultural events in space.					<B>Conclusion</B>: The street though it may be a public space has character and private domains. And though at times it harms the public space, in other help like with cultural and political events that occurs in this region thanks to the flow of people that circulate in place thanks to the commercial character of the road.				</P>
